# GitHub API Configuration
# Get your personal access token at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 
# Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://github.com/settings/tokens
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it a name like "repo-deployer"
# 4. Select scopes: check only "public_repo" (read-only access to public repositories)
# 5. Click "Generate token"
# 6. Copy the token (starts with "ghp_")
# 7. Paste it below
#
# Scopes needed: public_repo (read-only access to public repositories)
# 
# Optional: Leave empty to use unauthenticated mode (60 req/hour limit)
# With token: 5000 req/hour (100x higher, recommended for 4K+ repositories)
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY: Never commit the .env file to git!
#     The .env file is in .gitignore and should only exist on your machine.
#
GITHUB_TOKEN=your_github_token_here
